The paper deals with game theory (cs.GT) and distributed systems (cs.DS) in the context of a fault-prone environment. It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the calculation of the threshold for the existence of a Nash equilibrium. The use of optimization techniques to maximize the number of clients attracted to each server suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the neural and evolutionary computing category (cs.NE). Finally, the study of the social cost of the game could also place the paper in the social and information networks category (cs.SI).
